PM (PortManager) is a bash wrapper for FreeBSD ports system. It allows  
you to manage your applications from a single tool.

EXAMPLE USAGE

  Install a new app:

    pm install irc/irssi
    pm install www/apache22


  Remove a app:

    pm deinstall irc/irssi
    pm deinstall www/apache22


  Search for all IRC related apps:

    pm -nk search irc

  Show all packages, that are not required by any other installed packages:

    pm -l rmunused

  Update the ports tree:

    pm update cvsup.pl.freebsd.org
